## ❓ Q7: Why is accuracy not always a good metric?

👉 Depth check

### ✅ Strong Answer:

> Accuracy can be misleading in imbalanced datasets. For example, if 90% of data belongs to one class, predicting only that class gives high accuracy but poor performance. In such cases, precision, recall, and F1-score are better metrics.
> 

---

## ❓ Q8: What other metrics did you consider?

### ✅ Strong Answer:

> Depending on the problem:
> 
- Precision → when false positives matter
- Recall → when false negatives matter
- F1-score → balance between precision and recall
- RMSE → for regression tasks

