## ❓ Q9: Your RMSE is 26%. What does that mean?

👉 Many candidates fail here

### ✅ Strong Answer:

> RMSE measures the average error between predicted and actual values. A value of 26 means that on average, my predictions deviate by 26 units from actual values. Lower RMSE indicates better model performance.
